<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/9805> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #9805" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/25> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "p. 257-63" .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/9465> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #9465" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/10> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "ref. 425" .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/6528> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #6528" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/2> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Perhaps an Augur by 56 (Grueber, CRRBM 1.485f., which may however refer to an ancestor). See 50, Augurs." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/6519> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #6519" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/2> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/3> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "A probable member of this college of priests about 31 B. C. In a number of instances the exact date when a priest became a member of his college is not known, and the conjecture is based on evidence of seniority such as the date of the consulship or some other office. The list of the Quindecimviri is based on Miss Hoffman's observation that the names listed in connection with the Saecular Games in 17 B. C. are arranged in the order of entrance into the college (see AJPh 73 [19521289-294). The names given below are drawn from Miss Hoffman's dissertation, The Membership of the Four Major Colleges of Priests from 44 B. C. to 37 A. D. (Bryn Mawr, 1951, available in microfilm).     The vacancies caused by the civil wars and the proscriptions were promptly filled with partisans of Antony and Octavian or persons who were restored in 39 by the Treaty of Misenum, for in 36 Messalla Corvinus was added to the college as a supernumerary member. See Dio 48.36.4; 49.16.1; cf. 48.43.2." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/6470> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #6470" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/2> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Celebrated, probably as Proconsul, a triumph ex Hispania on April 27 (Fast. Barb., Degrassi 342f., 569; the number of the year is not given but was almost certainly 33 B. C.; see 32, Promagistrates, on Claudius Pulcher, and Cornificius). With the booty he restored the temple of Hercules and the Muses (Suet. Aug. 29.5; cf. Ovid Fast. 6.801; Tac. Ann. 3.72). See PIR 2.338, no. 173." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/6445> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #6445" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/2> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Governor of Spain, almost certainly as Proconsul, in succession to Norbanus Flaccus (see below, and cf. 35, Promagistrates) and before Claudius Pulcher." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/6413> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #6413" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/2> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Sent to Spain as Proconsul (Fast. Barb. for 33, Degrassi 342f., 569), probably before the end of 35, certainly by early in 34." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/6319> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #6319" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/2> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Fast. Mag. Vic., Degrassi 282f., 287f.; Fast. Biond., ibid. 291f.; and see 135, 506f.; on Cornelius, Forlati, Epigraphica 3 (1941) 272: C. Norbano, L. Lentulo Cos.; cf. Groag, Laur. Aquinc. 2.32, note 13; Degrassi 287f." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/5960> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #5960" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/2> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "He too is listed among those who might have been allotted a province and refused to recognize the validity of the allotment of provinces carried through in the Senate meeting on November 28 (Cic. Phil. 3.25)." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/5528> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #5528" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/2> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Vetoed the proposal to send Faustus Sulla to secure Mauretanian allies for Pompey (Caes. BC 1.6.4; see PIR 2.338, no. 173)." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/5506> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #5506" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/2> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Coins dated ca. 56 (Grueber, CRRBM 1.485f.) with the lituus as emblem." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/5498> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #5498" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/2> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/3> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "A probable member of the college of Augurs on the eve of the death of Hortensius." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/10151> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #10151" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/30> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Triumph ex Hispania. MRR II.416, Itgenshorst no. 284, Rich no. 285." .
